From Marc Thibault Subject Re PEM and MIME In article Edward Vielmetti writes I would suggest that attractive MIME formatted news messages a day would be sufficient to get a few people thinking about adding MIME support to news readers esp if the content is really worth But that's just the There is no such thing as MIME Formatted By analogy MIME is a content labelling standard for the box not a specification for the contents It provides a standard for like minded individuals to exchange mail containing an agreed upon data You say tomahto I say tomaeto you say postscript I say Cheers Marc Marc Thibault CIS Put another log NC FreeNet on the BEGIN PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK Version hihtneFrrn vuEcSavh HLnv END PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK